author: The Virginian-Pilot
title: Tuesday's multi-sport roundup | N. Academy wins showdown
text:
Boys soccer Norfolk Academy 3, Cape Henry 1
Taylor Acra, Ryan Fulmer and Dillon Jacob scored to rally the Bulldogs (9-1-1) past the Dolphins in a Tidewater Conference rivalry game on Tuesday.
Cape Henry grabbed a 1-0 lead midway through the first half before Acra equalized. Fulmer put the host Bulldogs on top and Jacob added the insurance goal with 10 minutes remaining.
Golf
5A South Region tournament
Hickory's Patrick Gareiss shot a 78 for sixth place after Day 1 at The Hamptons Golf Course.
Hickory (348) was fifth in the team standings.
Mills Godwin (315) led the competition, while Deep Run's Adam Hade carded a 1-over 72 for sole possession of first place.
South Hampton Roads' competitors include: Kempsville Ryan Oden in seventh, Kempsville's Mark Albert and Nansemond River's Andrew Halmrast tied for 12th and Salem's Mannie Mandoka in 16th.
Field hockey
First Colonial 8, Kellam 1
Cameron Strickland led the top-ranked Patriots (11-0) with four goals in a win over the No. 4 Knights.
Riley Taylor added two goals.
Cox 8, Tallwood 2
Alexis Gingerich recorded a hat trick, Leah Crouse had two goals and three assists, and the No. 3 Falcons beat the No. 8 Lions in a Coastal Conference game.
Cox's Alex Brewer netted a pair of goals.
Indian River 3, Norview 2
Abby Reed scored the winning goal with six minutes remaining in overtime for the Braves.
Nansemond-Suffolk 1, Norfolk Collegiate 0
Paige Christiansen scored the winning goal, on Summer Wood's assist, with two minutes remaining in overtime in the Saints' (7-2-1) shutout win.
Ocean Lakes 4, Landstown 0
Cady Thomas scored three goals and Jennifer Zeller earned the shutout for the Dolphins.
Girls volleyball
Ocean Lakes 3, First Colonial 1
Taylor Allbritten and Danielle Hart had 15 kills apiece and the No. 2 Dolphins (12-3) beat the No. 4 Patriots (11-4).
Hart and Lauren Zell combined for nine blocks for the Dolphins, who won 25-15, 25-23, 20-25, 25-17.
Hickory 3, Granby 0
Erin Parks tallied 12 kills and two aces as the No. 7 Hawks swept the No. 9 Comets 25-18, 25-22, 25-21.
Hickory's Natalie Eaton had four kills and Taylor Dean had three blocks.
Boys volleyball
Bishop Sullivan 3, Cape Henry 2
Jimmy Hine delivered 43 assists, Billy Weschler posted 19 kills and the 10th-ranked Crusaders (18-0) edged the No. 9 Dolphins 25-20, 16-25, 25-23, 22-25, 15-10 in a Tidewater Conference battle.
Bishop Sullivan's David Montague added 12 kills.
